00:39:31,402 --> 00:39:34,496
Well, thanks for your time.

492
00:39:45,950 --> 00:39:47,417
We need to talk.

493
00:40:01,633 --> 00:40:03,931
This better be important enough
to ruin my updo.

494
00:40:04,102 --> 00:40:05,433
I got a little spooked, okay?

495
00:40:05,970 --> 00:40:09,303
A detective came to my house,
I started thinking I could go to jail.

496
00:40:10,141 --> 00:40:12,200
We're in this together.
We could all go.

497
00:40:12,377 --> 00:40:15,574
That's bull shit. Okay, you have
a house and a brand-new Mercedes.

498
00:40:15,747 --> 00:40:18,807
I'm stuck living in a shack
with leaky pipes and water stains.

499
00:40:20,485 --> 00:40:24,148
You are set for life. If he dies,
you inherit everything.

500
00:40:24,322 --> 00:40:27,553
You're screwing me. can fee it.

501
00:40:27,725 --> 00:40:29,590
No, Brandi.

502
00:40:29,761 --> 00:40:32,161
That's so not true.

503
00:40:32,997 --> 00:40:34,464
I haven't seen you in days.

504
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:37,491
Brandi, you knew
it was gonna be like this.

505
00:40:37,669 --> 00:40:40,297
Yeah, but I didn't think
it was gonna be this hard.

506
00:40:40,471 --> 00:40:43,565
I'm all alone, okay?
You're out getting married.

507
00:40:43,741 --> 00:40:46,335
Okay. This is the only way...

508
00:40:46,511 --> 00:40:48,604
...that we could get you
some money right now.

509
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:53,342
And then, when Carson turns 30,
we hit the jackpot.

510
00:40:55,353 --> 00:40:56,342
Come here.

511
00:41:01,192 --> 00:41:03,353
You believe me, don't you?

512
00:41:22,180 --> 00:41:23,977
I'd like to introduce to you all...

513
00:41:24,148 --> 00:41:26,981
...Mr. and Mrs. Carson Wheetly.

514
00:41:45,970 --> 00:41:47,028
Who needs a drink?

515
00:41:51,476 --> 00:41:53,034
Happy, healthy...

516
00:41:53,211 --> 00:41:54,838
Wealthy and wise.

517
00:41:55,013 --> 00:41:56,913
Mrs. Wheetly.

518
00:42:01,819 --> 00:42:06,085
I just wanted to say that even though
we did this for practical reasons...

519
00:42:07,592 --> 00:42:09,560
...I’m really glad.

520
00:42:09,727 --> 00:42:11,592
I love you.

521
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:19,829
Baby, I love you too.

522
00:42:20,605 --> 00:42:23,005
We're gonna be so happy.

523
00:42:25,109 --> 00:42:27,942
What do you think we should do,
now that we're marred?

524
00:42:28,379 --> 00:42:29,368
I don't know.

525
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:34,780
Should we open our gifts and see
how many blenders we got?

526
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:37,613
I was thinking of something
a little more fun.

527
00:42:38,623 --> 00:42:40,215
Like wine glasses.

528
00:42:40,391 --> 00:42:41,619
A margarita set?

529
00:42:56,374 --> 00:42:58,968
What asshole
do you think forgot his keys?

530
00:43:01,212 --> 00:43:03,737
Call the valet, dickhead.

531
00:43:05,983 --> 00:43:07,473
Is this a bad time?

532
00:43:07,652 --> 00:43:09,142
Are you here to arrest me again?

533
00:43:09,320 --> 00:43:10,810
It's hotter than hell out here.

534
00:43:10,988 --> 00:43:13,218
Do you mind if I come in
and talk for a while?

535
00:43:16,994 --> 00:43:19,462
What can I help you with, detective?

536
00:43:20,064 --> 00:43:22,589
There's been some developments
in your father's case.

537
00:43:22,767 --> 00:43:25,565
When's the last time
you saw Shane Hendricks?

538
00:43:27,505 --> 00:43:29,132
The day before my father died.

539
00:43:31,342 --> 00:43:33,833
We raced boats right outside.

540
00:43:34,812 --> 00:43:36,905
Does he have
something to do with this?

541
00:43:37,081 --> 00:43:39,675
- I don't know, maybe.
- Did you talk to him?

542
00:43:39,851 --> 00:43:43,582
Yeah, he wasn't very cooperative.

543
00:43:44,856 --> 00:43:45,845
He hates cops.

544
00:43:46,023 --> 00:43:47,786
You know I kind of got that.

545
00:43:47,959 --> 00:43:49,358
You and he are friends, huh?

546
00:43:50,862 --> 00:43:52,853
He liked to come around
and piss off my dad.

547
00:43:53,030 --> 00:43:57,797
And yet, you chose to hang out
with him anyway, right?

548
00:43:58,703 --> 00:44:01,501
We were friends since we were kids.
We know the same people.

549
00:44:03,174 --> 00:44:06,007
Look, maybe I wanted
to piss off my dad too.

550
00:44:06,177 --> 00:44:08,372
Was Shane sleeping
with Brandi Cox?

551
00:44:10,448 --> 00:44:14,316
How should I know?
I never met her before the other day.

552
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:17,386
Oh, right. Right.

553
00:44:18,489 --> 00:44:19,820
She involved with this too?

554
00:44:21,325 --> 00:44:24,192
Damned if I know. Too early to tell.

555
00:44:24,362 --> 00:44:25,829
I wouldn't rule her out though.

556
00:44:25,997 --> 00:44:30,058
In fact, I wouldn't rule anyone out.

557
00:44:30,902 --> 00:44:34,668
You're probably anxious to get back
with your wife. Thanks for your time.

558
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:38,809
Oh, and you rest assured,
young man...

559
00:44:38,976 --> 00:44:41,706
...I will find your father's killer.

560
00:44:47,685 --> 00:44:49,152
He knows.

561
00:44:49,320 --> 00:44:51,015
He doesn't know anything.

562
00:44:51,189 --> 00:44:52,588
Did you tell him what we said?

563
00:44:52,757 --> 00:44:54,748
Yeah, that Shane hated my dad,
I told him.

564
00:44:54,926 --> 00:44:57,326
Then he asked about Brandi,
said she was a suspect.

565
00:44:57,495 --> 00:44:58,587
A suspect?

566
00:44:58,763 --> 00:45:01,027
- Yeah, might be a suspect.
- "Was" or "might be?"

567
00:45:01,199 --> 00:45:03,394
I don't know.
What difference does it make?

568
00:45:03,568 --> 00:45:04,592
He's on to her.

569
00:45:04,769 --> 00:45:08,227
Carson, we knew
he was gonna suspect Brandi.

570
00:45:08,773 --> 00:45:11,173
I'm pretty sure
that Brandi won't talk.

571
00:45:11,342 --> 00:45:14,277
Pretty sure? Jesus, Rach.
You said she was 100 percent.

572
00:45:14,445 --> 00:45:17,778
I know, I thought so.
But now I don't know.

573
00:45:17,949 --> 00:45:20,747
I didn't wanna tell you, before
the wedding she came to me...

574
00:45:20,918 --> 00:45:23,785
...and she just started talking
a I this crazy stuff...

575
00:45:23,955 --> 00:45:26,287
...about how she wasn't happy
with our arrangement.

576
00:45:35,466 --> 00:45:38,128
- She threaten you?
- This is why I didn't wanna tell you.

577
00:45:38,302 --> 00:45:39,735
I knew you'd get al worked up.

578
00:45:39,904 --> 00:45:42,737
- Rach, did she threaten you?
- Sort of.

579
00:45:46,911 --> 00:45:49,311
We gotta take care of her
before Walker to gets her.

580
00:45:51,482 --> 00:45:52,813
I'll set it up.

581
00:45:53,417 --> 00:45:54,907
Where?

582
00:45:57,288 --> 00:46:00,655
Tonight at the hotel
by the Glades.

583
00:46:05,997 --> 00:46:08,295
It's okay, we can do this.

584
00:46:18,809 --> 00:46:21,004
I'm worried about Walker.

585
00:46:21,912 --> 00:46:23,311
Hey, cap, you got a minute?

586
00:46:24,315 --> 00:46:28,581
Yeah. Larry, Larry, you know I can't
comment on an ongoing investigation.

587
00:46:31,522 --> 00:46:33,513
All right, yup, always a pleasure.

588
00:46:34,925 --> 00:46:37,155
Why the hell isn't that Ted Wheetly
case closed?

589
00:46:37,328 --> 00:46:39,956
Well, I was waiting for Forensics
to give me a report...

590
00:46:40,131 --> 00:46:42,190
...on that piece I found at the scene.

591
00:46:42,700 --> 00:46:44,964
- And?
- It's an intake manifold valve...

592
00:46:45,136 --> 00:46:47,832
...from a 1998 V10.
- So?

593
00:46:48,005 --> 00:46:50,701
So Ted would never let anything
in his car that wasn't new.

594
00:46:50,875 --> 00:46:54,003
This part in particular was recalled.
When the car hit 5000 rpm...

595
00:46:54,178 --> 00:46:57,045
...there was a good chance
that it would spark up and explode.

596
00:46:57,214 --> 00:46:59,682
Maybe we should all
get out of Dodge, you know?

597
00:46:59,850 --> 00:47:02,148
Wait for the money to land.
Let things cool down.

598
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:05,221
I don't think Carson wants you
to get a penny of his money.

599
00:47:05,389 --> 00:47:07,880
- The check's being sent to me.
- I think he's scheming.

600
00:47:08,526 --> 00:47:11,723
It's his birthright. He doesn't
want a couple of silly swamp girls...

601
00:47:11,896 --> 00:47:13,557
...to get their hands on it.

602
00:47:13,731 --> 00:47:15,665
Okay, any suspects?

603
00:47:16,233 --> 00:47:18,895
- Shane Hendricks.
- You're not serious.

604
00:47:19,070 --> 00:47:21,470
- I am serious.
- Do you know who his father is?

605
00:47:21,639 --> 00:47:24,005
Yes, the new ninth richest man
in Miami.

606
00:47:24,175 --> 00:47:27,076
When the money drops,
you and me will bolt town.

607
00:47:27,244 --> 00:47:29,235
We' cut our losses.
It's still $5 million.

608
00:47:29,413 --> 00:47:32,849
- It's plenty to get by on.
- I don't wanna just get by.

609
00:47:33,718 --> 00:47:35,743
We did this so we wouldn't have to.

610
00:47:35,920 --> 00:47:37,080
So what are you thinking?

611
00:47:38,989 --> 00:47:40,752
It's like you said.

612
00:47:41,158 --> 00:47:46,095
With Carson out of the way...
I mean, I'm the sole heir to his trust.

613
00:47:47,164 --> 00:47:48,597
I don't know about this, Rachel.

614
00:47:51,335 --> 00:47:53,860
Brandi, it's a little ate now
to be getting cold feet.

615
00:47:54,038 --> 00:47:55,027
Don't you think?

616
00:47:55,206 --> 00:47:57,868
- And you want me to bring him n?
- No, I didn't say that.

617
00:47:58,042 --> 00:48:01,409
I said he was a suspect. And no,
I do not want to bring him in yet.

618
00:48:01,579 --> 00:48:04,548
Not until I find out what's really
going on with Brandi Cox.

619
00:48:04,715 --> 00:48:07,115
The girl who got raped?
How is she involved?

620
00:48:07,284 --> 00:48:10,617
Something about her working for
Shane does not sit right with me.

621
00:48:11,422 --> 00:48:12,889
I need your help.

622
00:48:14,558 --> 00:48:17,459
Without it, we get nothing.

623
00:48:18,896 --> 00:48:19,885
When?

624
00:48:20,598 --> 00:48:24,932
We're meeting later tonight
at the hotel by the Glades.

625
00:48:31,375 --> 00:48:33,775
It's okay. We can do this.

626
00:48:35,312 --> 00:48:38,804
This is Blue Bay, not Miami. No se
complaints and the occasional drunk...

627
00:48:38,983 --> 00:48:41,247
...that's about all the excitement
we can handle.

628
00:48:41,419 --> 00:48:43,649
I won't have a homicide
cluttering up my backyard.

629
00:48:43,821 --> 00:48:46,813
- Now close it quick.
- I'm trying to do that, captain.

630
00:48:46,991 --> 00:48:51,792
Which is why I thought maybe I'd go
down to the Keys, poke around a bit.

631
00:48:51,962 --> 00:48:53,987
If you pay for my gas?

632
00:49:09,847 --> 00:49:12,839
Here, why don't you let me
help you with that?

633
00:49:13,017 --> 00:49:16,783
That's sweet. Hey, aren't you
Adam Klotsen's cousin?

634
00:49:16,954 --> 00:49:20,355
- I think I've seen you before.
- No. No. I'm...

635
00:49:20,524 --> 00:49:22,458
I'm looking for Darlene Cox.

636
00:49:22,626 --> 00:49:25,527
- You a cop?
- Yeah. Up at Blue Bay.

637
00:49:25,696 --> 00:49:28,859
- What do you want with Darlene?
- It's about her daughter Brand.

638
00:49:29,533 --> 00:49:31,967
I'm Darlene. What did she do?

639
00:49:32,536 --> 00:49:34,026
Nothing.

640
00:49:34,972 --> 00:49:36,803
I'm part of the rape investigation.

641
00:49:38,876 --> 00:49:40,366
She'd been raped?

642
00:49:40,544 --> 00:49:42,535
When's the last time
you spoke to her?

643
00:49:43,180 --> 00:49:45,171
Not since she and Rachel
left for school.

644
00:49:45,349 --> 00:49:47,715
I just knew something bad
would happen.

645
00:49:47,885 --> 00:49:50,012
No, no, she's...

646
00:49:51,388 --> 00:49:54,551
She's gonna be fine. Do you mind
if I ask you a few questions?

647
00:49:55,392 --> 00:49:58,657
- If you think it'll help.
- I think it will. You just said that...

648
00:50:00,397 --> 00:50:02,490
...she and Rachel
went to school together?

649
00:50:02,666 --> 00:50:05,032
Of course they did.
They was always together.

650
00:50:05,202 --> 00:50:09,229
It was like the two of them grew
from the same branch or something.

651
00:50:09,406 --> 00:50:13,308
I'm a little confused.
Well, I thought that you...

652
00:50:14,011 --> 00:50:16,741
I thought you used to clean
Rachel's estate.

653
00:50:18,148 --> 00:50:21,379
Estate? You mean
that old trailer up on bricks?

654
00:50:21,552 --> 00:50:24,817
Hell. the only thing that would
clean that is a great big hurricane...

655
00:50:24,989 --> 00:50:26,684
...f you know what I mean.

656
00:50:26,857 --> 00:50:29,052
Yeah. know what you...
So you're telling me...

657
00:50:29,226 --> 00:50:31,251
...that Rachel and Brandi
were best friends.

658
00:50:32,096 --> 00:50:33,495
Ever since they were girls.

659
00:50:33,664 --> 00:50:35,928
They'd go up in that cabin
all day in the woods.

660
00:50:36,100 --> 00:50:40,059
- Doing what?
- Just being kids, I guess.

661
00:50:40,237 --> 00:50:43,104
Brandi had a couple of old junkers
she was working on up there.

662
00:50:44,108 --> 00:50:47,771
Thing is, Rachel filled that girl's head
with all sorts of things.

663
00:50:47,945 --> 00:50:50,038
- What kind of things?
- Like the two of them...

664
00:50:50,214 --> 00:50:52,944
...they was gonna go find themselves
some rich husbands.

665
00:50:54,285 --> 00:50:56,617
I don't know where
they came up with that idea.

666
00:50:56,787 --> 00:50:58,220
And now look what happened.

667
00:50:58,889 --> 00:51:02,416
Yeah. One more question.

668
00:51:02,593 --> 00:51:05,118
Where's this old cabin
in the woods?

669
00:53:20,431 --> 00:53:24,561
Anderson. Frank Walker. I need you
to run a part number for me, all right?

670
00:53:25,335 --> 00:53:26,700
Yeah.

671
00:53:26,870 --> 00:53:31,273
I got a feeling it's gonna come up
as a '98 V10.

672
00:53:52,129 --> 00:53:54,620
Stick to the plan, you' I be fine.

673
00:54:05,809 --> 00:54:07,208
Damn.

674
00:54:16,153 --> 00:54:18,314
I ain't seen you in a while.

675
00:55:01,765 --> 00:55:03,494
Squeeze it.

676
00:55:14,678 --> 00:55:15,702
Do it!

677
00:55:19,349 --> 00:55:20,543
Rach, now!

678
00:55:22,553 --> 00:55:24,145
Do it!

679
00:55:24,321 --> 00:55:25,982
Do you think she's gonna kill me?

680
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:29,356
Rach, now.

681
00:55:53,650 --> 00:55:55,049
You backstabbing bitch!

682
00:56:23,947 --> 00:56:25,278
I am glad did it.

683
00:56:27,117 --> 00:56:28,914
You have blood all over your shirt.

684
00:56:29,086 --> 00:56:31,384
Here. take it off. I'll burn it.

685
00:56:32,456 --> 00:56:35,550
- Did you bring Carson's laptop?
- Yeah. It's in the duffle bag.

686
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:45,459
Okay. How does this sound?

687
00:56:46,536 --> 00:56:51,599
"I, Carson Wheetly, admit
to killing my father, Ted Wheetly."

688
00:56:51,775 --> 00:56:53,299
Go on.

689
00:56:53,477 --> 00:56:57,072
"He killed my mother.
He was a womanizer...

690
00:56:57,247 --> 00:57:00,444
...a drunk, and a violent man."

691
00:57:00,617 --> 00:57:06,647
"He got what he deserved, just like
this bullet will deliver what I deserve."

692
00:57:07,491 --> 00:57:11,222
No sign of a struggle.
No other prints.

693
00:57:11,395 --> 00:57:14,159
A note. Hell, my 2-year-o d
could've closed this one.

694
00:57:14,331 --> 00:57:15,628
So that's it?

695
00:57:15,799 --> 00:57:18,563
Crazy rich kid kills his father...

696
00:57:18,735 --> 00:57:21,795
...can't stand himself, so he comes
down here and shoots himself?

697
00:57:21,972 --> 00:57:23,166
- That's it?
- Open and shut.

698
00:57:24,841 --> 00:57:29,141
Yeah. Well, why did he drive
all the way down to the swamp?

699
00:57:29,313 --> 00:57:32,009
Why didn't he just
shoot himself at home?

700
00:57:32,182 --> 00:57:35,481
Detective, I invited you down here
as a courtesy...

701
00:57:35,652 --> 00:57:38,746
...because, well, this is your boy.

702
00:57:38,922 --> 00:57:41,857
But as far as the Everglades City P.D.
is concerned...

703
00:57:42,025 --> 00:57:44,858
...it’s stone crab time.

704
00:57:45,028 --> 00:57:48,327
- Did you notify the next of kin?
- She identified the body this morning.

705
00:58:17,728 --> 00:58:18,956
There you are, sir.

706
00:58:19,129 --> 00:58:20,562
Can I help you, detective?

707
00:58:20,731 --> 00:58:22,824
I'm sorry for your loss.

708
00:58:23,367 --> 00:58:26,666
I didn't know condolence calls
were part of the job.

709
00:58:28,705 --> 00:58:31,401
Must be one of the benefits
of being the ninth richest person...

710
00:58:31,575 --> 00:58:33,668
...n the State of Florida.

711
00:58:39,516 --> 00:58:43,316
This whole thing worked out
kind of nice for you.

712
00:58:44,154 --> 00:58:46,418
How all this worked out. isn't it?

713
00:58:51,595 --> 00:58:54,257
By nice you mean
losing my husband?

714
00:58:54,431 --> 00:58:55,420
No, no, no.

715
00:58:55,599 --> 00:58:59,057
By nice I mean by you finally
nabbing yourself a rich boy...

716
00:58:59,236 --> 00:59:00,760
...and all of his riches.

717
00:59:01,772 --> 00:59:03,763
So where'd you get that?

718
00:59:03,940 --> 00:59:06,534
The old cabin by your house.

719
00:59:06,710 --> 00:59:10,271
The cabin where you and Brandi Cox
plotted to find you a husband.

720
00:59:10,447 --> 00:59:13,280
- So what?
- Motive.

721
00:59:14,117 --> 00:59:17,382
That doesn't prove anything,
detective. Except that I'm poor...

722
00:59:17,554 --> 00:59:21,547
...and that I pretended not to be
because I was embarrassed by it.

723
00:59:21,725 --> 00:59:24,694
I just wanted to find myself
a good guy.

724
00:59:26,129 --> 00:59:27,255
That a crime?

725
00:59:27,431 --> 00:59:29,695
No, it's not a crime.

726
00:59:29,866 --> 00:59:34,735
And actually, coming from anyone
but you, it might be touching.

727
00:59:38,442 --> 00:59:41,275
You enjoy your trip
down memory lane.

728
00:59:41,445 --> 00:59:43,072
I'll see myself out.

729
01:00:17,914 --> 01:00:19,848
- Hello?
- Walker came by to visit.

730
01:00:20,016 --> 01:00:21,779
He had the file on Cason.

731
01:00:21,952 --> 01:00:23,010
How?

732
01:00:23,186 --> 01:00:25,017
- He was in the cabin.
