and drop your anchor on me.

972
01:19:48,250 --> 01:19:49,774
Last one home, slave for a day?

973
01:19:49,952 --> 01:19:53,115
- I might just let you win.
- I hope you do.

974
01:20:14,009 --> 01:20:17,035
Watch out for that
manifold intake valve.

975
01:20:22,017 --> 01:20:23,609
We did it.

976
01:20:46,475 --> 01:20:48,067
You Brandi?

977
01:20:49,411 --> 01:20:52,380
- Who are you?
- I want to talk about your father.

978
01:20:53,582 --> 01:20:55,743
- He's dead.
- I know.

979
01:20:55,918 --> 01:20:59,217
Your father was a good man.
He didn't deserve to die.

980
01:21:01,357 --> 01:21:03,587
I'm the guy who's gonna
help you get even.

981
01:21:04,526 --> 01:21:05,720
All right.

982
01:21:06,562 --> 01:21:08,086
How?

983
01:21:18,540 --> 01:21:20,599
He's just perfect, right?

984
01:21:34,356 --> 01:21:38,349
I just can't believe how bad y
your father treated your mother.

985
01:21:41,563 --> 01:21:44,464
She must have felt
there was no other way out.

986
01:21:45,801 --> 01:21:47,735
He's a murderer...

987
01:21:47,903 --> 01:21:50,428
...and nobody is gonna
see it like that.

988
01:21:51,974 --> 01:21:55,137
He'll get what's coming to him.
They always do.

989
01:21:55,978 --> 01:21:57,639
Bullshit.

990
01:21:58,280 --> 01:22:00,578
Guy walks on water.

991
01:22:04,987 --> 01:22:06,716
You know...

992
01:22:07,489 --> 01:22:10,481
...there is something
you can do about it.

993
01:22:12,327 --> 01:22:14,090
Like what?

994
01:22:24,173 --> 01:22:26,641
Breaking into Shane's garage
is a piece of cake.

995
01:22:26,809 --> 01:22:29,277
There's no security, no nothing.

996
01:22:29,445 --> 01:22:31,470
- There's no security.
- None.

997
01:22:31,647 --> 01:22:34,013
All you need to do is get his keys...

998
01:22:34,183 --> 01:22:36,014
...and et yourself n
through the door.

999
01:22:36,185 --> 01:22:37,743
How do we get his keys?

1000
01:22:37,920 --> 01:22:39,911
The guy's a total horn dog.

1001
01:22:40,088 --> 01:22:42,147
It shouldn't be too hard.

1002
01:22:49,865 --> 01:22:51,662
No... Hey, Hendricks!

1003
01:22:52,367 --> 01:22:54,597
What the hell are you doing
in my home?

1004
01:22:54,770 --> 01:22:56,328
Carson invited me.

1005
01:22:56,505 --> 01:22:58,097
Rachel.

1006
01:22:59,141 --> 01:23:01,439
You know that whole boat race
was my idea.

1007
01:23:01,610 --> 01:23:03,009
It doesn't matter.

1008
01:23:03,178 --> 01:23:05,009
He's an idiot.

1009
01:23:06,114 --> 01:23:08,309
He's not that bad.

1010
01:23:10,018 --> 01:23:11,713
It's just...

1011
01:23:16,291 --> 01:23:19,055
He gets to have all the fun.

1012
01:23:19,228 --> 01:23:21,219
You're mad at him.

1013
01:23:22,998 --> 01:23:24,556
Yeah?

1014
01:23:24,733 --> 01:23:26,394
So what?

1015
01:23:41,383 --> 01:23:43,510
He gets nothing
unless he gets married.

1016
01:23:43,685 --> 01:23:45,812
He has no interest in that.

1017
01:23:45,988 --> 01:23:47,922
What are we supposed to do,
wait 10 years?

1018
01:23:48,090 --> 01:23:50,081
Oh, yeah, right.
Like that will help.

1019
01:23:50,259 --> 01:23:51,487
He'll totally cut us out.

1020
01:23:51,660 --> 01:23:55,528
Well, then we need to convince him
it's in his best interest to get married.

1021
01:23:56,532 --> 01:23:58,830
Like if he needed to pay me off.

1022
01:24:00,369 --> 01:24:03,497
Like if he didn't, he'd go to jail.

1023
01:24:04,072 --> 01:24:06,700
All right, how?

1024
01:24:07,209 --> 01:24:09,109
I could say he raped me.

1025
01:24:10,746 --> 01:24:11,906
You guys set me up?

1026
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:13,707
Baby, just re ax.

1027
01:24:14,750 --> 01:24:16,615
Listen, you're not thinking straight.

1028
01:24:16,785 --> 01:24:19,083
If we don't get married,
we don't get a penny.

1029
01:24:19,254 --> 01:24:22,587
I mean this way, we get
some of the trust every year...

1030
01:24:22,758 --> 01:24:27,457
...plus we get a big payout
up front that we can all split.

1031
01:24:27,629 --> 01:24:30,894
- I mean, that's a win-win.
- For you. I'm in jail.

1032
01:24:31,066 --> 01:24:32,465
You can get out real easy.

1033
01:24:33,602 --> 01:24:35,593
By agreeing to get married.

1034
01:24:35,771 --> 01:24:36,965
If you don't...

1035
01:24:37,139 --> 01:24:40,404
...I’m really afraid that Brandi's
gonna go through with those charges.

1036
01:24:40,576 --> 01:24:43,636
She thinks you're gonna
cut her out when you're 30.

1037
01:24:44,580 --> 01:24:47,242
What about your friend, Linda?

1038
01:24:47,416 --> 01:24:51,477
- Did you tell her about Dad?
- No, I didn't tell her a thing.

1039
01:24:51,653 --> 01:24:55,384
As far as she's concerned
it was a scam to get the estate.

1040
01:24:56,992 --> 01:25:00,985
She just needed cash for,
I don't know, her year abroad.

1041
01:25:07,502 --> 01:25:08,833
George, where have you been?

1042
01:25:09,004 --> 01:25:10,733
I got here as soon as I could.

1043
01:25:28,190 --> 01:25:30,181
- I'm a little worried.
- About what?

1044
01:25:30,359 --> 01:25:32,452
What if Walker suspects me
for killing Rachel?

1045
01:25:32,628 --> 01:25:35,688
We've been through this. You shoot
her, you feed her to the gators.

1046
01:25:35,864 --> 01:25:39,265
Plant the bag in her house
and tip off the police. I know, baby.

1047
01:25:39,434 --> 01:25:41,026
But what if Walker doesn't buy it?

1048
01:25:41,203 --> 01:25:44,297
He seems smarter
than I imagined him to be.

1049
01:25:45,974 --> 01:25:47,464
Then we buy him.

1050
01:25:47,643 --> 01:25:51,511
I have known Frank for a while now.
He's as crooked as they come.

1051
01:26:04,893 --> 01:26:08,329
Pretty convenient how these
just happened to be there.

1052
01:26:08,497 --> 01:26:09,657
She's a bad crook.

1053
01:26:09,831 --> 01:26:11,492
Well, you're worse.

1054
01:26:11,667 --> 01:26:14,898
Guy lives next to the cabin, nice
old trucker, invited me for a beer.

1055
01:26:15,070 --> 01:26:18,198
He tells me he saw you
this morning carrying that bag.

1056
01:26:18,373 --> 01:26:22,070
He remembers you very well because
he almost ran you over one day.

1057
01:26:23,712 --> 01:26:28,547
Memory fits you to a tee,
your comp ex on, your height.

1058
01:26:29,151 --> 01:26:31,585
His memory is bulletproof.

1059
01:26:34,723 --> 01:26:38,215
How would you like
an early retirement, detective?

1060
01:27:00,282 --> 01:27:01,442
We did it.

1061
01:27:10,892 --> 01:27:12,621
How about you buy me a drink?

1062
01:27:12,794 --> 01:27:15,422
How about buy you
the whole damn bar?
